Predstavenie datasetu

N dataset obsahuje informcie o ovzdu a meracch staniciach ktor dan merania vykonvali. Je zloen z dvoch sborov a to: - measurements.csv - stations.csv ## Skratky: - PM2.5 - Particulate Matter (g/m3)
- PM10 - Particulate Matter (g/m3)
- NOx - Nitrogen Oxides (g/m3)
- NO2 - Nitrogen Dioxide (g/m3)
- SO2 - Sulfur Dioxide (g/m3)
- CO - Carbon Monoxide emissions (g/m3)
- CO2 - Carbon Dioxide (g/m3)
- PAHs - Polycyclic Aromatic Hydrocarbons (g/m3)
- NH3 - Ammonia trace (g/m3)
- Pb - Lead (g/m3)
- TEMP - Temperature (degree Celsius)
- DEWP - Dew point temperature (degree Celsius)
- PRES - Pressure (hPa, <100, 1050>)
- RAIN - Rain (mm)
- WSPM - Wind Speed (m/s)
- WD - Wind Direction
- VOC - Volatile Organic Compounds
- CFCs - Chlorofluorocarbons
- C2H3NO5 - Peroxyacetyl nitrate
- H2CO - Plywood emit formaldehyde
- GSTM1 - Glutathione-S transferase M1
- 1-OHP - 1-hydroxypyrene
- 2-OHF - 2-hydroxyfluorene
- 2-OHNa - 2-hydroxynaphthalene
- N2 - Nitrogen
- O2 - Oxygen
- O3 - Ozone
- Ar - Argon
- Ne - Neon
- CH4 - Methane
- He - Helium
- Kr - Krypton
- I2 - Iodine
- H2 - Hydrogen
- Xe - Xenon

helper

parse_dates <- function(date_string) {
  formats <- c("%Y/%m/%d", "%d %b %Y", "%Y-%m-%d", "%m/%d/%Y, %H:%M:%S", "%d/%m/%Y, %H:%M:%S")

  for (format in formats) {
    parsed_date <- as.POSIXct(date_string, format = format, tz = "")
    if (!is.na(parsed_date)) {
      # urob datum na format "28 Aug 2016"
      return(format(parsed_date, "%d %b %Y"))
    }
  }

  return(NA)
}
# Kontrola jedinench hodnt a ich potu
revision_count <- table(labor_stations$revision)
#revision_count
# Nahradenie pecifickch hodnt
labor_stations$revision <- sapply(labor_stations$revision, parse_dates)
cat('Identifikovan rozdielne formty dtumu sme zjednotili na formt dd mmm yyyy')

outliers_list <- lapply(df_out, function(column) {
  IQR_value <- IQR(column, na.rm = TRUE)
  upper_bound <- quantile(column, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE) + 1.5 * IQR_value
  lower_bound <- quantile(column, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE) - 1.5 * IQR_value
  lower_outliers <- which(column < lower_bound)
  upper_outliers <- which(column > upper_bound)
  return(list(lower_outliers = lower_outliers, upper_outliers = upper_outliers))
})


plot(df_out[[1]], main=paste("Outliers in", names(df_out)[1]), col="blue", pch=19)
if(length(outliers_list[[1]]$lower_outliers) > 0) {
  points(outliers_list[[1]]$lower_outliers, df_out[outliers_list[[1]]$lower_outliers, 1], col="red", pch=19)
}
if(length(outliers_list[[1]]$upper_outliers) > 0) {
  points(outliers_list[[1]]$upper_outliers, df_out[outliers_list[[1]]$upper_outliers, 1], col="red", pch=19)
}

Rozdelme dta na trnovacie a testovacie a vytvorme Model

set.seed(123)
sample <- sample(c(TRUE, FALSE), nrow(df), replace = TRUE, prob = c(0.5, 0.3))
train_data <- df[sample,]
test_data <- df[!sample,]

# PM2.5  the most harmful pollution
# PM10 - Particulate Matter (g/m3)
# SO2 - Sulfur Dioxide  (g/m3)
# CO - Carbon Monoxide emissions  (g/m3)
PM25Model <- lm(PM2.5 ~ PM10  + SO2 + CO, data = train_data)
summary(PM25Model)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = PM2.5 ~ PM10 + SO2 + CO, data = train_data)
##

## F-statistic:  2405 on 3 and 15103 DF,  p-value: < 2.2e-16

Vyhodnotenie na zklade summary

  • Odhadovan tandardn chyba rezidul je 1.588, o naznauje rozptyl rezidulnych hodnt okolo regresnej iary.
  • F-statisticsje 2405 na 3 a 15103 DF, s p-hodnotou menou ako 2.2e-16, o naznauje, e model ako celok je tatisticky vznamn. (m va F-statistics tm lepie)
  • Std. Error je na nzkch hodnotch, tak meme poveda e chybovos modelu m meniu pravdepodobnost
  • r-squared by malo is viac k 1 aby to bolo presnejie
  • p-value je < 0.05 model je tatisticky signifikantn
  • t-value je celkom na vysokch hodnotch o me naznaova koeficient regresie nieje tatisticky vznamn

Vy-plotujeme si model

par(mar = c(1, 1, 1, 1))
plot(PM25Model)

Vyhodnotenie plotov

Residuals vs Fitted - erven iara by mala horizontlna najviac ako je mon - Ak je iara nakriven moe to znamena nelinerny vzah - Detekuje odlahl body

Normal QQ - Kontrolujeme i residuals maj normlovu distribciu - Ak s rezdu normlne distribuovan, body na grafe by mali vytvori pribline priamu iaru - Ak s body na Q-Q grafe zakriven alebo maj in netandardn vzory, me to naznaova, e rezdu maj neobvykl rozdelenie - V naom prpade to vyzer e residualy maj normlov distribciu

Scale-Location (Spread location) - iara je takmer horizontlna take mohli by sme poveda e residuals s rovnomerne rozloen

Residuals vs Leverage: - zobrazuje ovplivnujce asti - nieo podobn ako outliery - ak by sme videli v rohoch iary tak je mon e to nieje v poriadku

Predikovanie na zklade testovacch dta + manulne overenie

predicted_values <- predict(PM25Model, newdata = test_data)

# PM25 = 12.88 - 0.11 * PM10 - 0.23 * SO2 + 0.10 * CO
cat("Expected: 5.72081 , Predicted: ",predict(PM25Model,data.frame(PM10=5.85838,  SO2=11.00024, CO=7.00959)))
## Expected: 5.72081 , Predicted:  8.114608
mean_absolute_error <- mean(abs(predicted_values - test_data$PM2.5))
mean_squared_error <- mean((predicted_values - test_data$PM2.5)^2)
root_mean_squared_error <- sqrt(mean_squared_error)

data.frame(Metric = c("Mean Absolute Error", "Mean Squared Error", "Root Mean Squared Error"), Value = c(mean_absolute_error,mean_squared_error,root_mean_squared_error))
##                    Metric    Value
## 1     Mean Absolute Error 1.255622
## 2      Mean Squared Error 2.448739
## 3 Root Mean Squared Error 1.564845

Vyhodnotenie na zklade metrk

MAE - meria absolutnu chybu medzi predikovanmi hodnotami a skutonmy

MSE - meria priemernu velkost chyb p redikciach modelu, a tak kvantifikuje rozdiel medzi skutonmi a predikovanmi hodnotami

RMSE -> poskytuje prehlad o tom ako dobre model predikuje alebo ako blzko s predikcie k skutonm hodnotm

  • V tomto prpade vetky prediktvne premenn maj vznamn vplyv na premenn

Predikcia na teste

# vpoet predpoved logistickej regresie na zklade predtm natrnovanho modelu
probabilities <- predict(logisticModel, newdata = testData, type = "response")

# Na zklade vrtench pravdepodobnost priraujeme triedy
# Ak je pravdepodobnos via ako 0.5, prirad sa hodnota reprezentujca TRUE warning
# Ak je menia alebo rovn 0.5, prirad sa FALSE warning
glmPredictions <- ifelse(probabilities > 0.5, levels(testData$warning)[2], levels(testData$warning)[1])

# konvertuje predpovedan hodnoty na faktorov premenn s rovami definovanmi v originlnej premennej
glmPredictions <- factor(glmPredictions, levels = levels(testData$warning))

Evaluacia modelu

confMatrix <- table(Predicted = glmPredictions, Actual = testData$warning)
print(confMatrix)
##          Actual
## Predicted    0    1
##         0 1542  604
##         1 1391 3699

confusionMatrix je tabuka, ktor ukazuje poty sprvnych a nesprvnych predikci modelu v porovnan s aktulnymi hodnotami. V tomto prpade s predictions predpovedan hodnoty z modelu, a testData$warning s skuton hodnoty cieovej premennej. Objekt confMat potom obsahuje tto metriku spolu s almi tatistikami vkonu modelu.

confMat <- confusionMatrix(glmPredictions, testData$warning)
confMatMatrix <- as.matrix(confMat$table)

Melt men confMatMatrix do dlhho formtu. Dlh formt je uiton pre vizualizciu, pretoe kad riadok reprezentuje jednu hodnotu s prslunmi identifiktormi. Vsledn objekt confMatMelted m tri stpce: - jeden pre skuton hodnoty - jeden pre predpovedan hodnoty - a jeden pre poet pozorovan pre kad kombinciu skutonch a predpovedanch hodnt

confMatMelted <- melt(confMatMatrix)
# Actual - predstavuje skuton hodnoty
# Predicted - predikovan hodnoty
# Value - poet prpadov pre kad kombinciu skutonej a predpovedanej hodnoty
colnames(confMatMelted) <- c('Actual', 'Predicted', 'Value')

Kontatovanie vsledkov

# Vytvorenie ROC objektu
roc_obj <- roc(testData$warning, probabilities)
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
# Vpis ROC krivky
plot(roc_obj, main="ROC Krivka")

# Hadanie optimlneho cut-off bodu
# Zvyajne chceme maximalizova Youdenov index (J), ktor je definovan ako sensitivity + specificity - 1
coords(roc_obj, "best", best.method="youden")
##   threshold specificity sensitivity
## 1 0.5518007   0.6137061   0.7859633

Vrti naprklad: - threshold (cut-off bod) - je hodnota, ktor sli ako hranica na rozhodovanie medzi dvoma monosami
- specificity - pravdepodobnos, e model predpoved pozitvny vsledok pozorovania, ke je vsledok skutone pozitvny
- sensitivity - pravdepodobnos, e model predpoved negatvny vsledok pozorovania, ke je vsledok skutone negatvny

# Vypotajme krivku ROC a njdime optimlny point
roc_obj <- roc(testData$warning, probabilities)
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
optimal <- coords(roc_obj, "best", best.method="youden")
optimal_threshold <- optimal$threshold

# Kontrola platnosti optimlnych sradnc
if (!is.null(optimal$x) && !is.null(optimal$y)) {
  # Plot ROC curve
  plot(roc_obj, main="ROC Curve with Optimal Threshold")

  # bod pre optimal threshold
  points(optimal$x, optimal$y, pch=19, col="red")

  # pridaj text label pre optimal threshold
  text(optimal$x, optimal$y, labels=paste("Threshold:", round(optimal_threshold, 3)), pos=4)
    segments(optimal$x, optimal$y, optimal$x, 0, col="red", lty=2)
} else {
  cat("Optimal coordinates are not available.\n")
}
## Optimal coordinates are not available.
p <- ggplot(confMatMelted, aes(x = Actual, y = Predicted, fill = Value)) +
  geom_tile(color = "white") +  # Tiles for each combination of actual and predicted
  geom_text(aes(label = Value), color = "black", size = 5) +  # prida text pre kazdu dladicu
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "white", high = "steelblue") +  # farba gradientu
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, vjust = 1, size = 12, hjust = 1)) +  # prida x-axis text
  xlab('Predicted') +  # X-axis label
  ylab('Actual') +  # Y-axis label
  ggtitle('Confusion Matrix - Logistic Regression')  # title
  • av horn dladica (604) predstavuje prav negatva (TN): prpady, ke model sprvne predpovedal negatvnu triedu.
  • av spodn dladica (1542) predstavuje falon negatva (FN): prpady, ke model nesprvne predpovedal negatvnu triedu, hoci v skutonosti bola pozitvna.
  • Prav horn dladica (3699) predstavuje prav pozitva (TP): prpady, ke model sprvne predpovedal pozitvnu triedu.
  • Prav spodn as (1391) predstavuje falon pozitvne vsledky (FP): prpady, ke model nesprvne predpovedal pozitvnu triedu, hoci v skutonosti bola negatvna.
print(p)

library(glmnet)

sample2 <- sample(c(TRUE, FALSE), nrow(df), replace = TRUE, prob = c(0.5, 0.3))
train_data <- df[sample2,]
test_data <- df[!sample2,]

# Nastavenie cieovej hodnoty na PM2.5
y_train_data <- train_data$PM2.5
y_test_data <- test_data$PM2.5

# Nastavenie nezvislch premennch na PM10, SO2 a CO a vytvorenie matice dt
x_train_data <- data.matrix(train_data[, c('PM10', 'SO2', 'CO')])
x_test_data <- data.matrix(test_data[, c('PM10', 'SO2', 'CO')])


x_train_data_SO2_CO <- data.matrix(train_data[, c('SO2', 'CO')])
x_test_data_SO2_CO <- data.matrix(test_data[, c('SO2', 'CO')])


x_train_data_C2H3NO5_NH3_PM10 <- data.matrix(train_data[, c('C2H3NO5', 'NH3', 'PM10')])
x_test_data_C2H3NO5_NH3_PM10<- data.matrix(test_data[, c('C2H3NO5', 'NH3', 'PM10')])

# Vytvorenie modelu
# cv = Cros validation pre njdenie optimlnej hodnoty pre Lambdu
# gausiann -> dvame vedie e robme linernu regresiu
cv_model <- cv.glmnet(x_train_data, y_train_data, alpha = 1, family = "gaussian")
cv_model_SO2_CO <- cv.glmnet(x_train_data_SO2_CO, y_train_data, alpha = 1, family = "gaussian")
cv_model_C2H3NO5_NH3_PM10 <- cv.glmnet(x_train_data_C2H3NO5_NH3_PM10, y_train_data, alpha = 1, family = "gaussian")

# Urenie optimlnej hodnoty lambda z krovej validcie
#hyperparameter lambda () - vyvauje kompromis medzi odchlkou a rozptylom vo vslednch koeficientoch.
best_lambda <- cv_model$lambda.min
best_lambda_SO2_CO <- cv_model_SO2_CO$lambda.min
best_lambda_C2H3NO5_NH3_PM10 <- cv_model_C2H3NO5_NH3_PM10$lambda.min


# Vykreslenie grafu krovej validcie
plot(cv_model)

# Zskanie koeficientov najlepieho modelu
best_model <- glmnet(x_train_data, y_train_data, alpha = 1, lambda = best_lambda)
best_model_SO2_CO <- glmnet(x_train_data_SO2_CO, y_train_data, alpha = 1, lambda = best_lambda_SO2_CO)
best_model_C2H3NO5_NH3_PM10 <- glmnet(x_train_data_C2H3NO5_NH3_PM10, y_train_data, alpha = 1, lambda = best_lambda_C2H3NO5_NH3_PM10)

y_predicted_S02_CO <- predict(best_model_SO2_CO, s = best_lambda_SO2_CO, newx = x_test_data_SO2_CO)
y_predicted_C2H3NO5_NH3_PM10 <- predict(best_model_C2H3NO5_NH3_PM10, s = best_lambda_C2H3NO5_NH3_PM10, newx = x_test_data_C2H3NO5_NH3_PM10)

SVM

SVM s typom algoritmu uenia pod dohadom, ktor sa pouva na klasifikan aj regresn lohy. S obzvl vkonn pre vysokorozmern daje. Cieom SVM je njs najlepiu oddeujcu hyperplochu, ktor rozdeuje rzne triedy v priestore prznakov. Vektory, ktor definuj hyperplochu, sa nazvaj podporn vektory.

Kernel je metda pouvan v SVM, ktor umouje uenie vo vysokodimenzionlnych priestoroch prznakov bez explicitnej transformcie dajov do tchto dimenzi. Je to uiton najm vtedy, ke hranica medzi triedami nie je linerna. Pouitm funkcie jadra me SVM vykonva zloit klasifikcie pomocou linerneho klasifiktora implicitnm mapovanm vstupnch dajov do vysokodimenzionlnych priestorov prznakov.

Radial Basis Function (RBF) Kernel

Kernel RBF je jednou z najbenejch funkci pouvanch v SVM. Oznauje sa aj ako Gaussov kernel. Vhody pouitia jadra RBF v SVM - RBF jadro je vemi flexibiln a doke riei prpady, ke je vzah medzi znakami tried a atribtmi nelinerny. - Funguje dobre vo vysokodimenzionlnych priestoroch, aj ke je poet dimenzi v ako poet vzoriek. - Je inn v scenroch, kde dtov body nie s linerne oddeliten. #### Others kernel options available in e1071: - Linear Kernel: This kernel is the simplest, where the prediction is based on the linear combination of the features. Its used when the data is linearly separable. You can specify it with kernel = linear. - Polynomial Kernel: This kernel allows for curved boundaries in the feature space. Its defined by the degree of the polynomial. Higher degrees can fit more complex structures but also risk overfitting. It can be specified using kernel = polynomial, and you can also set the degree with the degree parameter. - Radial Basis Function (RBF) Kernel: Also known as the Gaussian kernel, this is a popular choice for many classification problems. It can map the data into an infinite-dimensional space and is effective in handling non-linear relationships. Its used with kernel = radial. - Sigmoid Kernel: This kernel functions like the sigmoid function in logistic regression. It can be specified with kernel = sigmoid. This is similar to a two-layer, perceptron neural network.

set.seed(123)
index <- sample(seq_len(nrow(df)), round(0.7 * nrow(df)))
trainData <- df[index,]
testData <- df[-index,]

# trenovanie SVM modelu

Porovnanie ROC kriviek

# Vpoet ROC kriviek pre kad model
glm_roc <- roc(response = testData$warning, predictor = as.numeric(glmPredictions))
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
lda_roc <- roc(response = testData$warning, predictor = as.numeric(ldaPredictions))
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
svm_roc <- roc(response = testData$warning, predictor = as.numeric(svmPredictions))
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
lda_rocTweak1 <- roc(response = testData$warning, predictor = as.numeric(ldaPredictionsTweak1))
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
svm_rocTweak1 <- roc(response = testData$warning, predictor = as.numeric(svmPredictionsTweak1))
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
svm_rocTweak2 <- roc(response = testData$warning, predictor = as.numeric(svmPredictionsTweak2))
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
# Vykreslenie ROC kriviek
plot(glm_roc, main="ROC Curves", col="red")
plot(lda_roc, add=TRUE, col="blue")
plot(svm_roc, add=TRUE, col="green")
plot(lda_rocTweak1, add=TRUE, col="black")
plot(svm_rocTweak1, add=TRUE, col="pink")
plot(svm_rocTweak2, add=TRUE, col="orange")
legend("bottomright", legend=c("GLM", "LDA", "SVM", "LDA_TWEAK1", "SVM_TWEAK1", "SVM_TWEAK2"), col=c("red", "blue", "green", "black", "pink", "orange"), lwd=2)

Heatmapy pre Confusion Matrix

# Pomocn funkcia na premenu zmtkovej matice na data frame vhodn pre ggplot
conf_matrix_to_df <- function(conf_matrix) {
  df <- as.data.frame(as.table(conf_matrix))
  colnames(df) <- c("Prediction", "Reference", "Frequency")  # Menme nzvy stpcov pre zrozumitenos a sprvne mapovanie
  return(df)
}

# Prevod zmtkovch matc na data frame
glm_df <- conf_matrix_to_df(glmConfMatrix$table)
lda_df <- conf_matrix_to_df(ldaConfMatrix$table)
svm_df <- conf_matrix_to_df(svmConfMatrix$table)
lda_df_Tweak1 <- conf_matrix_to_df(ldaConfMatrixTweak1$table)
svm_df_Tweak1 <- conf_matrix_to_df(svmConfMatrixTweak1$table)
svm_df_Tweak2 <- conf_matrix_to_df(svmConfMatrixTweak2$table)

# Funkcia na vykreslenie heatmapy
plot_conf_matrix <- function(data, title) {
  ggplot(data, aes(x = Prediction, y = Reference, fill = Frequency)) +
          geom_tile(color = "white") +
          scale_fill_gradient(low = "blue", high = "red") +
          theme_minimal() +
          theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
          labs(title = title, x = 'Predicted Class', y = 'Actual Class') +
          geom_text(aes(label = Frequency), vjust = 1.5, color = "white")
}

# Vykreslenie heatmap pre kad zmtkov maticu
plot_conf_matrix(glm_df, "GLM Confusion Matrix")

plot_conf_matrix(lda_df, "LDA Confusion Matrix")

plot_conf_matrix(svm_df, "SVM Confusion Matrix")

plot_conf_matrix(lda_df_Tweak1, "LDA Tweak1 Confusion Matrix")

plot_conf_matrix(svm_df_Tweak1, "SVM Tweak1 Confusion Matrix")

plot_conf_matrix(svm_df_Tweak2, "SVM Tweak2 Confusion Matrix")

Precision-Recall Curve and AUPRC:

Plocha pod krivkou PR (AUPRC) kvantifikuje celkov vkon klasifikanho modelu. Vypotava plochu pod krivkou PR, ktor predstavuje schopnos modelu dosiahnu vysok presnos a vysok odvolvku sasne pri vetkch monch prahovch hodnotch. vyia hodnota AUPRC naznauje lepiu vkonnos modelu, pretoe znamen viu plochu pod krivkou PR, o naznauje, e model me dosiahnu vysok presnos a vysok odvolvku pri rznych prahovch hodnotch. AUPRC je obzvl uiton pri prci s nevyvenmi sbormi dajov, kde jedna trieda prevlda ovea viac ako druh, pretoe sa zameriava na vkonnos pozitvnej triedy, ktor me by zaujmavejia. v shrne krivka Precision-Recall poskytuje prehad o kompromise medzi presnosou a odvolvkou pri rznych klasifikanch prahoch, zatia o AUPRC sumarizuje celkov vkonnos modelu pri vetkch monch prahoch. Oba s cennmi nstrojmi na hodnotenie innosti klasifikanch modelov, najm v scenroch, kde je prtomn nerovnovha tried.

# Generovanie kriviek PR s parametrom krivky nastavenm na TRUE
# curve parameter musi byt true ak chem plotovat krivku
pr_glm <- pr.curve(scores.class0 = glmPredictions, weights.class0 = testData$warning == 1, curve = TRUE)
pr_lda <- pr.curve(scores.class0 = ldaPredictions, weights.class0 = testData$warning == 1, curve = TRUE)
pr_svm <- pr.curve(scores.class0 = svmPredictions, weights.class0 = testData$warning == 1, curve = TRUE)
pr_lda_Tweak1 <- pr.curve(scores.class0 = ldaPredictionsTweak1, weights.class0 = testData$warning == 1, curve = TRUE)
pr_svm_Tweak1 <- pr.curve(scores.class0 = svmPredictionsTweak1, weights.class0 = testData$warning == 1, curve = TRUE)
pr_svm_Tweak2 <- pr.curve(scores.class0 = svmPredictionsTweak2, weights.class0 = testData$warning == 1, curve = TRUE)

F1 Score

Precision

meria presnos pozitvnych predpoved modelu. Odpoved na otzku: Koko zo vetkch prpadov, ktor model predpovedal ako pozitvne, bolo skutone pozitvnych? Matematicky sa presnos vypota ako: Vysok presnos znamen, e model m tendenciu robi menej falone pozitvnych predpoved.

Recall (Sensitivity or True Positive Rate)

meria schopnos modelu sprvne identifikova pozitvne prpady z celkovho potu skutonch pozitvnych prpadov. Odpoved na otzku: Koko zo vetkch skutonch pozitvnych prpadov model sprvne predpovedal ako pozitvne? Vysok sptn vzba znamen, e model zachytva vinu skutonch pozitvnych prpadov.

F1 Score

je harmonick priemer Precision a Recall, ktor poskytuje jedin metriku na vyvenie Precision a Recall. Je uiton najm vtedy, ke potrebujete rovnako zohadni falone pozitvne aj falone negatvne vsledky. SkreF1 dosahuje najlepiu hodnotu pri 1 (dokonal presnos a odvolanie) a najhoriu pri 0.

# extrahujem precision a recall z confusion matrices
precision_glm <- glmConfMatrix$byClass['Pos Pred Value']
recall_glm <- glmConfMatrix$byClass['Sensitivity']
f1_glm <- 2 * (precision_glm * recall_glm) / (precision_glm + recall_glm)

precision_lda <- ldaConfMatrix$byClass['Pos Pred Value']
recall_lda <- ldaConfMatrix$byClass['Sensitivity']
f1_lda <- 2 * (precision_lda * recall_lda) / (precision_lda + recall_lda)

precision_svm <- svmConfMatrix$byClass['Pos Pred Value']
recall_svm <- svmConfMatrix$byClass['Sensitivity']
f1_svm <- 2 * (precision_svm * recall_svm) / (precision_svm + recall_svm)

precision_lda_Tweak1 <- ldaConfMatrixTweak1$byClass['Pos Pred Value']
recall_lda_Tweak1<- ldaConfMatrixTweak1$byClass['Sensitivity']
f1_lda_Tweak1 <- 2 * (precision_lda_Tweak1 * recall_lda_Tweak1) / (precision_lda_Tweak1 + recall_lda_Tweak1)

precision_svm_Tweak1 <- svmConfMatrixTweak1$byClass['Pos Pred Value']
recall_svm_Tweak1 <- svmConfMatrixTweak1$byClass['Sensitivity']
f1_svm_Tweak1 <- 2 * (precision_svm_Tweak1 * recall_svm_Tweak1) / (precision_svm_Tweak1 + recall_svm_Tweak1)

precision_svm_Tweak2 <- svmConfMatrixTweak2$byClass['Pos Pred Value']
recall_svm_Tweak2 <- svmConfMatrixTweak2$byClass['Sensitivity']
f1_svm_Tweak2 <- 2 * (precision_svm_Tweak2 * recall_svm_Tweak2) / (precision_svm_Tweak2 + recall_svm_Tweak2)
